FreeMaths attempts to detect and format mathematics as you type. Use ^ for powers and / for fractions. Formatting of expressions follows the rules of @precedence so you may need to add brackets (particularly for denominators).

You may prevent a word from being displayed as mathematics by preceding it with a ''.

Maths symbols can be entered using the provided buttons or by using the shortcut key combinations (hover over the button to learn the shortcut).

Lower and upper limits can be added using _ and ^. E.g. for ∫_1^3 enter '∫_1^3
Multi-character limits must be entered within {} brackets. You may need to add a '' to the start of the limit to prevent it being computed (see calculations below). E.g. for ∫_π^{'2π} enter '∫_π^{'2π}

Where your expression cannot be parsed FreeMaths will still attempt to format it using <a href='https://khan.github.io/KaTeX/function-support.html'>Katex</a>. Katex error messages are displayed to help you correct any problems.

FreeMaths will calculate anything you enclose in {}. E.g. '{1/6+1/3} gives {1/6+1/3}
Angles default to radians so you may need to add a degree symbol. You may also use ,dp and ,sf to round your answers.
E.g. '{sin(23°),2dp} gives {sin(23°),2dp}

FreeMaths aims to make communicating with mathematics as easy as possible. Please contact us if there is anything you would like help with.
